The paper focuses on a GPU-accelerated self-join algorithm for high dimensional data, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses optimizations for reducing the number of distance calculations, which is a common problem in computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper mentions using the algorithm for image processing (cs.CV), which is another potential sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses achieving good scalability for multi-GPU or distributed-memory self-joins, which falls under the category of parallel and distributed computing (cs.DC).
